WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.636 --> 00:00:15.181
-[Japanese rock theme music playing]
-[lyrics in Japanese]

2
00:01:27.796 --> 00:01:30.715
[in English] ♪ Don't be. be. be afraid ♪

3
00:01:31.341 --> 00:01:35.470
♪ Don't be. be. be. be. be afraid ♪

4
00:01:35.553 --> 00:01:41.017
BAKI-DOU: THE INVINCIBLE SAMURAI

5
00:01:43.770 --> 00:01:47.023
[Musashi] I also crave that success
in the modern world!

6
00:01:47.107 --> 00:01:48.900
[dramatic music sting]

7
00:01:52.862 --> 00:01:54.364
-[slicing]
-[metallic thunk]

8
00:01:55.365 --> 00:01:56.365
Hmm?

9
00:01:56.866 --> 00:01:58.284
[Tokugawa] He… he… he cut him?

10
00:02:05.416 --> 00:02:08.503
Well now. isn't that something!

11
00:02:09.129 --> 00:02:12.549
That body of yours is surprisingly firm.

12
00:02:12.632 --> 00:02:15.301
It didn't feel like
it was made of flesh and blood.

13
00:02:16.177 --> 00:02:18.012
No. it felt more like hitting armor.

14
00:02:18.096 --> 00:02:19.556
a full suit of it too.

15
00:02:20.473 --> 00:02:22.308
My blade didn't penetrate.

16
00:02:22.892 --> 00:02:25.895
And there's many a man
who've fallen to that slash.

17
00:02:26.396 --> 00:02:30.316
This is the first time I've not been able
to sever the collarbone.

18
00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:31.568
[Yujiro chuckles]

19
00:02:33.069 --> 00:02:35.071
That was disappointing.

20
00:02:35.155 --> 00:02:36.573
[dramatic music sting]

21
00:02:37.907 --> 00:02:40.702
You didn't even bother drawing your sword.

22
00:02:40.785 --> 00:02:43.746
but you're surprised
you can't cut through my flesh?

23
00:02:44.414 --> 00:02:47.167
Is it swordplay or wordplay?

24
00:02:49.169 --> 00:02:50.169
[glass shattering]

25
00:02:53.173 --> 00:02:54.591
[gasping]

26
00:02:58.761 --> 00:03:00.096
Mitsunari.

27
00:03:00.180 --> 00:03:03.600
Can you bring him a sword?
I can tell he wants one.

28
00:03:06.186 --> 00:03:07.854
-[dramatic music sting]
-[Musashi] Hmm.

29
00:03:07.937 --> 00:03:10.607
A kind gesture from a strong man.

30
00:03:10.690 --> 00:03:12.317
[tense music playing]

31
00:03:14.194 --> 00:03:16.237
[unsettling battle music playing]

32
00:03:18.031 --> 00:03:20.325
Feels nice to be properly armed again.

33
00:03:21.326 --> 00:03:23.161
Very nice indeed.

34
00:03:23.828 --> 00:03:25.580
[Tokugawa] Oh…

35
00:03:32.670 --> 00:03:33.670
Hmm?

36
00:03:36.090 --> 00:03:37.759
Oh!

37
00:03:37.842 --> 00:03:39.260
You're brash!

38
00:03:39.344 --> 00:03:41.012
[Tokugawa] Oh!

39
00:03:43.806 --> 00:03:44.806
Miyamoto.

40
00:03:46.226 --> 00:03:47.518
don't get cocky.

41
00:03:52.106 --> 00:03:54.275
[gravel clattering]

42
00:03:55.360 --> 00:03:56.778
Oh!

43
00:04:09.123 --> 00:04:10.250
[Yujiro grunts]

44
00:04:10.333 --> 00:04:12.543
[air whooshing]

45
00:04:14.128 --> 00:04:16.047
[tense battle music continues]

46
00:04:18.633 --> 00:04:19.884
[Musashi] Oh…

47
00:04:20.385 --> 00:04:22.095
Look at that.

48
00:04:22.178 --> 00:04:26.307
I was close to wandering with the dead.
but with no memory of being struck.

49
00:04:27.225 --> 00:04:31.312
The martial artists of the modern world
have taught me an important lesson.

50
00:04:32.146 --> 00:04:36.317
They possess a state of mind only reached
with the absence of swords.

51
00:04:36.401 --> 00:04:39.821
Fists can reach
the lethal level of a blade.

52
00:04:40.697 --> 00:04:41.697
However…

53
00:04:43.199 --> 00:04:44.199
Hmm.

54
00:04:44.784 --> 00:04:47.829
…the "sword of Musashi"
is not just any blade.

55
00:04:47.912 --> 00:04:49.580
[Yujiro snarls]

56
00:04:49.664 --> 00:04:52.333
[Musashi] Let's see how strong you are!
Hold on tight!

57
00:04:52.417 --> 00:04:53.835
[cracking boom]

58
00:04:53.918 --> 00:04:54.919
[Musashi grunts]

59
00:05:00.174 --> 00:05:02.427
[narrator] The Ogre grabbed the sword.

60
00:05:02.510 --> 00:05:03.845
Don't let go!

61
00:05:03.928 --> 00:05:05.805
[narrator] But he got hold of the blade.

62
00:05:05.888 --> 00:05:09.600
The one gripping the hilt
was Musashi Miyamoto.

63
00:05:09.684 --> 00:05:11.352
[shocked gasping]

64
00:05:11.436 --> 00:05:13.104
[Musashi grunts loudly]

65
00:05:16.190 --> 00:05:17.190
[Musashi grunts]

66
00:05:18.443 --> 00:05:21.112
-[dramatic music playing]
-[Yujiro] Hmm?

67
00:05:22.864 --> 00:05:24.115
[music fades]

68
00:05:24.198 --> 00:05:25.867
Not already?

69
00:05:26.617 --> 00:05:28.619
[chuckles]

70
00:05:28.703 --> 00:05:32.123
You have a particular talent
for not holding back.

71
00:05:32.206 --> 00:05:34.876
He's using Niten Ichi-ryu this early.

72
00:05:35.460 --> 00:05:36.627
I like that.

73
00:05:37.503 --> 00:05:39.964
[narrator] Standing face to face
with a man like this

74
00:05:40.048 --> 00:05:41.966
demands you hold nothing back.

75
00:05:42.467 --> 00:05:44.385
[unsettling music playing]

76
00:05:47.472 --> 00:05:48.765
[chattering excitedly]

77
00:05:48.848 --> 00:05:51.142
I just can't contain myself!

78
00:05:53.978 --> 00:05:55.646
It's so exciting!

79
00:05:58.941 --> 00:06:00.902
[narrator] To meet every attack head-on

80
00:06:00.985 --> 00:06:03.154
and crush it in its tracks.

81
00:06:04.739 --> 00:06:09.243
that approach became synonymous
with the "strongest creature alive."

82
00:06:09.744 --> 00:06:11.245
It was his legacy.

83
00:06:12.288 --> 00:06:15.166
When was the last time
he had dodged anything?

84
00:06:17.752 --> 00:06:19.170
[Tokugawa] Look at their auras!

85
00:06:19.754 --> 00:06:22.673
Is there an apt analogy
for this deathly energy?

86
00:06:23.257 --> 00:06:26.177
Two fearsome kings of beasts
in a standoff?

87
00:06:26.803 --> 00:06:28.930
Perhaps a tiger and a dragon?

88
00:06:29.013 --> 00:06:31.432
No. that still doesn't do it justice.

89
00:06:32.016 --> 00:06:33.935
Those don't even come close.

90
00:06:34.519 --> 00:06:37.939
I could try all day. but the truth is.
when it comes to strength.

91
00:06:38.523 --> 00:06:43.945
these two great men standing before me
are utterly unmatched in this world!

92
00:06:44.028 --> 00:06:45.530
I'm sure of it!

93
00:06:46.280 --> 00:06:49.700
Lions. dragons. tigers.

94
00:06:49.784 --> 00:06:53.830
none of them could defeat
either of these powerful fighters.

95
00:06:53.913 --> 00:06:57.542
[narrator] Musashi went limp.
letting the strength drain from his body.

96
00:06:57.625 --> 00:07:01.087
and with that acceleration.
he pushed off from his heel.

97
00:07:01.671 --> 00:07:04.715
and directed his momentum
towards his opponent.

98
00:07:04.799 --> 00:07:07.218
closing the distance in a blink.

99
00:07:08.177 --> 00:07:10.638
Using the full length of his blade.

100
00:07:11.180 --> 00:07:14.225
he directed his slash
at a vital vulnerability.

101
00:07:14.892 --> 00:07:17.228
But Yujiro could see it coming.

102
00:07:17.311 --> 00:07:22.233
and he understood all of this
in less than 0.000 seconds.

103
00:07:22.316 --> 00:07:24.235
[bones crunching]

104
00:07:24.318 --> 00:07:27.113
Look at those
well-trained wrists of yours.

105
00:07:28.573 --> 00:07:29.991
-[impact thudding]
-[Musashi groans]

106
00:07:30.074 --> 00:07:31.617
[tense music intensifies]

107
00:07:33.703 --> 00:07:35.163
[pained grunting]

108
00:07:36.622 --> 00:07:37.999
[groaning]

109
00:07:39.333 --> 00:07:41.252
[sword slicing]

110
00:07:41.335 --> 00:07:42.503
[flesh squelching]

111
00:07:45.882 --> 00:07:50.011
[narrator] Even if he lost consciousness.
Musashi would never let go of his swords.

112
00:07:52.096 --> 00:07:54.015
But it was pain
that tore them from him now.

113
00:07:54.098 --> 00:07:57.018
Unlike anything he had ever experienced.

114
00:07:57.602 --> 00:08:00.021
Not even the throes of war could compare.

115
00:08:00.104 --> 00:08:01.397
[Tokugawa] Huh?!

116
00:08:01.481 --> 00:08:02.398
[gasps]

117
00:08:02.482 --> 00:08:03.774
It's over!

118
00:08:05.109 --> 00:08:06.110
Huh?

119
00:08:06.611 --> 00:08:08.029
[gravel crunching]

120
00:08:08.112 --> 00:08:08.988
[groaning]

121
00:08:09.071 --> 00:08:10.551
[narrator] In the midst of his agony.

122
00:08:11.532 --> 00:08:15.036
an unprompted thought sprouted
in Musashi's mind.

123
00:08:15.119 --> 00:08:16.537
[Tokugawa] Or maybe not.

124
00:08:17.246 --> 00:08:18.539
[Musashi] It's almost ready.

125
00:08:19.582 --> 00:08:23.002
The secret technique
that I was developing in Higo.

126
00:08:24.170 --> 00:08:26.047
[Tokugawa] It's not over yet.

127
00:08:26.797 --> 00:08:28.299
Impressive strength.

128
00:08:29.425 --> 00:08:31.010
May I ask for your name?

129
00:08:31.636 --> 00:08:34.388
I can't think of anyone better
to try it on.

130
00:08:35.181 --> 00:08:36.098
SWORD

131
00:08:36.182 --> 00:08:39.352
[narrator] Standard script evolved
into semi-cursive script.

132
00:08:39.894 --> 00:08:41.938
That in turn became cursive script.

133
00:08:42.605 --> 00:08:46.442
So then. what is that equivalency
in swordsmanship?

134
00:08:47.527 --> 00:08:50.696
And… what is its evolution?

135
00:08:50.780 --> 00:08:52.198
MUSASHI MIYAMOTO
58 YEARS OLD

136
00:08:59.288 --> 00:09:00.331
Oh…

137
00:09:00.915 --> 00:09:02.708
He's 58 years old.

138
00:09:02.792 --> 00:09:06.712
but even in his old age. he still has
such an intimidating presence.

139
00:09:07.296 --> 00:09:11.217
It's almost as if he were wielding
his long and short swords.

140
00:09:12.426 --> 00:09:14.971
[Musashi] It's not like
I can cut you down.

141
00:09:15.638 --> 00:09:17.723
so why are you hesitating?

142
00:09:17.807 --> 00:09:18.808
[gasps]

143
00:09:19.809 --> 00:09:20.809
[man] Now!

144
00:09:22.061 --> 00:09:23.980
[gasps] What? When did he?!

145
00:09:24.063 --> 00:09:25.481
[all gasping]

146
00:09:26.566 --> 00:09:27.733
First here.

147
00:09:27.817 --> 00:09:29.485
Then here. Stab here.

148
00:09:29.569 --> 00:09:32.738
-Slash. slash. slash. slash.
-[pained grunting]

149
00:09:33.447 --> 00:09:34.490
Hmm.

150
00:09:35.324 --> 00:09:37.493
[man wailing softly]

151
00:09:38.578 --> 00:09:39.787
[gasps loudly]

152
00:09:41.372 --> 00:09:42.999
-Now you're in pieces.
-[gasps]

153
00:09:43.666 --> 00:09:44.500
I am?

154
00:09:44.584 --> 00:09:47.253
-[confused muttering]
-[Musashi] Continue your practice.

155
00:09:47.336 --> 00:09:49.755
[men whispering]

156
00:09:50.423 --> 00:09:52.008
[Musashi] I'm getting close.

157
00:09:53.718 --> 00:09:55.636
-[gasps]
-Getting close?

158
00:09:55.720 --> 00:09:57.513
What's going on?

159
00:09:57.597 --> 00:10:01.642
Master seems to be taking up his swords
less and less as time goes on.

160
00:10:01.726 --> 00:10:03.436
It's almost spring again.

161
00:10:03.519 --> 00:10:06.647
and yet I don't think
he's picked them up even once all year.

162
00:10:09.734 --> 00:10:11.861
[Musashi] What lies beyond cursive script?

163
00:10:11.944 --> 00:10:13.654
And what lies beyond that?

164
00:10:14.655 --> 00:10:17.033
It began with me writing
on paper every day.

165
00:10:17.992 --> 00:10:20.036
Entire days spent writing.

166
00:10:20.119 --> 00:10:24.040
until eventually I began writing
not on paper. but in my head.

167
00:10:24.624 --> 00:10:27.043
Entire days spent writing in my head.

168
00:10:28.127 --> 00:10:30.546
So much so that when I looked at a wall.

169
00:10:31.380 --> 00:10:33.299
I envisioned the writing on it.

170
00:10:34.175 --> 00:10:35.801
When I gazed at a waterfall.

171
00:10:36.469 --> 00:10:38.554
I conjured the words to write on it.

172
00:10:38.638 --> 00:10:40.348
[intriguing music playing]

173
00:10:42.141 --> 00:10:44.060
[Musashi] Even the great arc of the sky

174
00:10:44.685 --> 00:10:47.313
became a surface for my brush to trace.

175
00:10:48.272 --> 00:10:50.107
And upon reaching this state.

176
00:10:51.567 --> 00:10:53.861
I no longer needed a brush.

177
00:10:54.987 --> 00:10:56.322
It's just the same

178
00:10:58.157 --> 00:11:00.076
for swords as well.

179
00:11:02.703 --> 00:11:05.081
They will become unnecessary.

180
00:11:05.164 --> 00:11:06.374
[music fades]

181
00:11:08.793 --> 00:11:10.503
[Yujiro] My last name's Hanma.

182
00:11:10.586 --> 00:11:13.005
And my first name's Yujiro.

183
00:11:13.089 --> 00:11:16.425
Otherwise known as
"The Strongest Creature on Earth."

184
00:11:17.009 --> 00:11:18.260
So they say.

185
00:11:18.344 --> 00:11:20.012
Huh.

186
00:11:20.680 --> 00:11:23.516
You are strong. Yujiro Hanma.

187
00:11:24.225 --> 00:11:25.768
[chuckles] Look at this.

188
00:11:25.851 --> 00:11:27.269
[dramatic music stab]

189
00:11:28.187 --> 00:11:30.314
In order to deliver
that kick to the groin.

190
00:11:30.398 --> 00:11:31.774
I had to let you wound me.

191
00:11:31.857 --> 00:11:35.111
You're strong too.
You live up to your reputation.

192
00:11:35.194 --> 00:11:37.530
Nah. you might be stronger.

193
00:11:38.489 --> 00:11:40.032
My reputation?

194
00:11:40.116 --> 00:11:43.035
So people have been talking about me
for 400 years?

195
00:11:43.703 --> 00:11:45.788
That's a thought that I can enjoy.

196
00:11:46.622 --> 00:11:47.790
I understand

197
00:11:47.873 --> 00:11:50.793
this is the most powerful man
in the world.

198
00:11:50.876 --> 00:11:52.837
Isn't that right. Tokugawa?

199
00:11:53.838 --> 00:11:56.799
Yes. Musashi. that's exactly who he is.

200
00:11:56.882 --> 00:12:00.094
The man who you see
standing before you now

201
00:12:00.177 --> 00:12:03.305
represents the "highest peak of strength"
in all the world.

202
00:12:05.891 --> 00:12:07.810
[sheathing sword]

203
00:12:11.731 --> 00:12:12.731
Huh?

204
00:12:14.191 --> 00:12:16.110
[Musashi] I'm returning these to you.

205
00:12:18.112 --> 00:12:19.572
[Tokugawa] Oh…

206
00:12:21.657 --> 00:12:23.033
I'm lucky.

207
00:12:23.117 --> 00:12:26.412
An opportunity for progress
has landed right in my lap!

208
00:12:27.872 --> 00:12:30.583
I'm still in some pain. but I can fight.

209
00:12:33.878 --> 00:12:34.878
Let's go.

210
00:12:36.422 --> 00:12:40.092
[Yujiro] As soon as he gave up his swords.
his aura only increased.

211
00:12:40.843 --> 00:12:43.179
Oh. I see. He didn't give 'em up at all.

212
00:12:46.182 --> 00:12:49.602
[Musashi] I don't need a large sword
or a small one.

213
00:12:49.685 --> 00:12:51.854
That is the way of my Niten Ichi-ryu.

214
00:12:55.191 --> 00:12:56.358
[slicing]

215
00:12:56.442 --> 00:12:57.860
[uneasy groaning]

216
00:12:58.611 --> 00:13:00.362
He's just as deadly without them!

217
00:13:00.446 --> 00:13:02.114
[Musashi] This is auspicious. indeed.

218
00:13:02.698 --> 00:13:04.867
He will bring it to fruition.

219
00:13:05.451 --> 00:13:08.621
The completion of Niten Ichi-ryu is here!

220
00:13:08.704 --> 00:13:11.123
I understand what's going on.

221
00:13:11.207 --> 00:13:13.751
You're close
to not needing physical swords.

222
00:13:13.834 --> 00:13:15.377
That's why you use two.

223
00:13:16.462 --> 00:13:17.880
Hmm.

224
00:13:17.963 --> 00:13:19.715
[slicing]

225
00:13:20.466 --> 00:13:21.884
[all gasping]

226
00:13:22.676 --> 00:13:23.886
Motobe!

227
00:13:23.969 --> 00:13:25.638
-[Tokugawa screams]
-Who is this?

228
00:13:28.265 --> 00:13:30.142
[Yujiro grunts] You bastard!

229
00:13:31.727 --> 00:13:33.395
What do you think you're doing?!

230
00:13:33.479 --> 00:13:34.939
[ominous music playing]

231
00:13:36.482 --> 00:13:39.902
How dare you try to protect
someone like me?!

232
00:13:41.487 --> 00:13:42.404
[Tokugawa] Wait!

233
00:13:42.488 --> 00:13:45.157
All right. That's enough. Yujiro.

234
00:13:45.241 --> 00:13:47.910
Now you're trying to get in my way?

235
00:13:47.993 --> 00:13:49.662
Wait! Stop. stop!

236
00:13:49.745 --> 00:13:51.914
Please calm yourself. Yujiro.

237
00:13:51.997 --> 00:13:54.416
Can't you see
Motobe jumped in to stop this?

238
00:13:55.209 --> 00:13:57.419
And look at what happened to him!

239
00:13:58.254 --> 00:14:00.506
I'm the last person
who wants to admit this.

240
00:14:00.589 --> 00:14:04.635
but this match has been rendered invalid.

241
00:14:11.559 --> 00:14:13.811
[dazed grunting]

242
00:14:15.187 --> 00:14:16.313
Huh?

243
00:14:18.399 --> 00:14:19.316
[gasps]

244
00:14:19.400 --> 00:14:21.902
[slicing]

245
00:14:23.821 --> 00:14:25.990
-[Tokugawa] You're awake.
-Huh?

246
00:14:26.907 --> 00:14:29.827
[Tokugawa] You did
something awfully extreme.

247
00:14:29.910 --> 00:14:31.412
Where are they now?

248
00:14:31.495 --> 00:14:34.331
I'm not really sure.
but they left the estate together.

249
00:14:35.791 --> 00:14:37.209
Is that so?

250
00:14:38.294 --> 00:14:40.838
Yes. I'll admit that it was extreme.

251
00:14:40.921 --> 00:14:42.381
but. Tokugawa.

252
00:14:42.464 --> 00:14:45.175
if I hadn't stepped in
and stopped them when I did.

253
00:14:45.259 --> 00:14:47.720
the Ogre likely would have been cut down.

254
00:14:47.803 --> 00:14:48.637
[Tokugawa] Hmm.

255
00:14:48.721 --> 00:14:50.222
-[Motobe] Unfortunately…
-Hmm?

256
00:14:50.306 --> 00:14:53.976
…everyone's understanding
of marital arts is far too shallow.

257
00:14:54.059 --> 00:14:56.312
Huh. So?

258
00:14:57.479 --> 00:15:00.482
So I. Izo Motobe. have come to help you.

259
00:15:03.235 --> 00:15:05.237
I don't really know how you could help.

260
00:15:05.321 --> 00:15:06.488
Watch out!

261
00:15:06.572 --> 00:15:08.741
-[slicing]
-[Tokugawa yells]

262
00:15:08.824 --> 00:15:13.495
[Motobe] In the next match.
it'll be I who cuts down Musashi.

263
00:15:15.080 --> 00:15:18.459
[narrator] Their outfits alone
were not enough to attract attention.

264
00:15:19.084 --> 00:15:23.756
No. it was their individuality.
their presence. their auras.

265
00:15:23.839 --> 00:15:26.508
It was impossible not to notice them.

266
00:15:26.592 --> 00:15:29.219
and so they both stood out from the crowd.

267
00:15:29.303 --> 00:15:31.597
Particularly since they were together.

268
00:15:32.097 --> 00:15:35.768
Yujiro Hanma. are you a famous person?

269
00:15:36.477 --> 00:15:38.520
Everyone seems interested in you.

270
00:15:39.146 --> 00:15:41.774
The people in front of us
can't hide their stares.

271
00:15:41.857 --> 00:15:44.276
and those behind us
have turned around to look.

272
00:15:44.360 --> 00:15:45.360
[chuckles]

273
00:15:45.819 --> 00:15:47.363
I think you're part of it.

274
00:15:48.614 --> 00:15:50.824
[narrator] It was simply too astonishing.

275
00:15:51.867 --> 00:15:54.286
[Tokugawa] All right. I understand.

276
00:15:54.912 --> 00:15:57.539
You are a practitioner
of ancient martial arts.

277
00:15:57.623 --> 00:16:00.000
so you want to be the next
to fight Musashi.

278
00:16:00.501 --> 00:16:04.046
But even more. you think
you can cut down the master swordsman.

279
00:16:04.129 --> 00:16:05.965
Is that out of the question?

280
00:16:06.048 --> 00:16:09.551
A match
between Musashi Miyamoto and myself?

281
00:16:10.511 --> 00:16:12.304
I think it's a good idea.

282
00:16:12.388 --> 00:16:15.307
I imagine it would be
an interesting battle.

283
00:16:15.391 --> 00:16:16.642
[Tokugawa] Hmm.

284
00:16:20.062 --> 00:16:21.855
It makes no difference to me if...

285
00:16:21.939 --> 00:16:23.816
-[Motobe] Don't lie to me!
-Huh?

286
00:16:23.899 --> 00:16:26.610
"Motobe. quit running your mouth."

287
00:16:26.694 --> 00:16:28.612
"Know your place. Izo!"

288
00:16:29.279 --> 00:16:31.281
I know that's what you want to say.

289
00:16:31.365 --> 00:16:33.951
I don't know about that. I. um…

290
00:16:34.034 --> 00:16:38.539
If anyone has a problem.
then they can come and face me directly.

291
00:16:39.039 --> 00:16:42.042
If someone comes to you
and says that I'm not strong enough.

292
00:16:42.126 --> 00:16:44.712
then we'll test their theory in battle.

293
00:16:45.379 --> 00:16:46.463
One stipulation.

294
00:16:47.214 --> 00:16:50.217
everything is permissible.
except the use of weapons.

295
00:16:50.300 --> 00:16:53.220
I have no need for such a paltry rule.

296
00:16:53.303 --> 00:16:55.014
Everything is allowed.

297
00:16:55.097 --> 00:16:58.726
Acquired knowledge. skills. tools.

298
00:16:59.309 --> 00:17:01.103
and of course. weaponry.

299
00:17:01.186 --> 00:17:03.731
From projectiles to smoke bombs.

300
00:17:03.814 --> 00:17:07.484
I want them to be prepared
for that kind of fight.

301
00:17:07.568 --> 00:17:09.528
[narrator] It was at that moment.

302
00:17:09.611 --> 00:17:13.032
Mitsunari would later acknowledge
that was when he decided.

303
00:17:13.824 --> 00:17:15.993
[Tokugawa] Motobe is a fit challenger!

304
00:17:24.209 --> 00:17:25.502
[gulps] Mm!

305
00:17:25.586 --> 00:17:27.004
A strong one.

306
00:17:27.087 --> 00:17:28.756
It is whiskey.

307
00:17:30.549 --> 00:17:32.760
-Mm.
-[Musashi] No. I mean that man.

308
00:17:35.262 --> 00:17:36.638
Izo's practical.

309
00:17:37.222 --> 00:17:39.433
Yes. that he is.

310
00:17:39.933 --> 00:17:41.894
but I am enjoying the drink as well.

311
00:17:42.644 --> 00:17:43.854
Oh? Oh!

312
00:17:44.938 --> 00:17:47.107
[Yujiro] The legends say
you couldn't drink.

313
00:17:47.191 --> 00:17:48.275
[Musashi] Couldn't drink?

314
00:17:48.859 --> 00:17:51.028
I'd say you have good taste in booze.

315
00:17:51.111 --> 00:17:54.531
Motobe seems willing
to use any means available.

316
00:17:54.615 --> 00:17:56.533
[intriguing music playing]

317
00:17:56.617 --> 00:17:57.618
[Musashi] And to be fair.

318
00:17:57.701 --> 00:18:00.287
compared to some of the others
I've fought here…

319
00:18:00.913 --> 00:18:01.914
[sighs quizzically]

320
00:18:01.997 --> 00:18:03.791
…he has quite the arsenal.

321
00:18:08.462 --> 00:18:10.047
A varied one at that.

322
00:18:10.839 --> 00:18:12.800
And there was proof of that today.

323
00:18:13.759 --> 00:18:16.887
He kept them hidden. but you saw them.

324
00:18:17.930 --> 00:18:21.809
[Musashi] Yes. concealed weapons.
He had them all over his person.

325
00:18:23.644 --> 00:18:25.062
[Yujiro] Hmm.

326
00:18:25.145 --> 00:18:27.147
It worked out for him.

327
00:18:27.231 --> 00:18:28.315
Worked out how?

328
00:18:29.191 --> 00:18:31.568
[Yujiro] This was an unexpected twist.

329
00:18:31.652 --> 00:18:36.740
He spent years mastering dead techniques
and ancient weapons.

330
00:18:36.824 --> 00:18:38.826
It all seemed like a waste.

331
00:18:38.909 --> 00:18:41.537
Even now. weapons like swords and spears.

332
00:18:41.620 --> 00:18:44.206
they're viewed
as valuable cultural assets.

333
00:18:44.289 --> 00:18:45.707
but smoke bombs?

334
00:18:45.791 --> 00:18:48.210
Grappling hooks? Weighted chains?

335
00:18:48.794 --> 00:18:51.588
His tools and techniques. ninjutsu…

336
00:18:52.172 --> 00:18:54.216
When the hell was he going to use that?

337
00:18:55.134 --> 00:18:58.178
Even in my era.
there were a few opportunities.

338
00:18:58.262 --> 00:19:01.098
A martial art that I thought was useless.

339
00:19:01.181 --> 00:19:03.350
but now. an opponent has appeared

340
00:19:03.433 --> 00:19:06.603
on whom he can use
every one of those talents.

341
00:19:06.687 --> 00:19:09.857
Skills that should have been
buried in obscurity

342
00:19:09.940 --> 00:19:11.358
come to light again.

343
00:19:12.067 --> 00:19:13.569
It's all thanks to you.

344
00:19:15.529 --> 00:19:16.613
Huh.

345
00:19:18.073 --> 00:19:20.617
You're a kinder man than I expected.

346
00:19:24.580 --> 00:19:25.622
Well. now.

347
00:19:25.706 --> 00:19:28.375
[man] It's been a while hasn't it. Sensei?

348
00:19:29.084 --> 00:19:31.128
Your words were full of resolve.

349
00:19:31.211 --> 00:19:33.005
So. you were listening?

350
00:19:33.088 --> 00:19:34.131
[man] Yes. sir.

351
00:19:34.214 --> 00:19:36.133
I was hiding in the attic.

352
00:19:36.216 --> 00:19:39.386
I had a feeling that it was you.
Good work. Gaia.

353
00:19:39.469 --> 00:19:41.889
MOTOBE-RYU JUJUTSU

354
00:19:41.972 --> 00:19:43.891
[intriguing music playing]

355
00:19:43.974 --> 00:19:46.727
[Gaia] I've been to this dojo
many times before.

356
00:19:46.810 --> 00:19:48.395
but every time I come back.

357
00:19:48.478 --> 00:19:52.149
my heart beats in my chest
like a child at play.

358
00:19:53.400 --> 00:19:55.152
[Motobe] I take it you like weapons?

359
00:19:55.235 --> 00:19:57.696
They're so cool. All of them.

360
00:19:57.779 --> 00:20:00.324
[laughs] You think they're cool?

361
00:20:00.407 --> 00:20:01.658
Weapons are amazing!

362
00:20:02.534 --> 00:20:05.746
Their shape and form perfectly match
their intended purpose.

363
00:20:06.246 --> 00:20:08.665
A tool that is the essence of necessity.

364
00:20:09.374 --> 00:20:12.169
The idea of requirement made physical.

365
00:20:12.252 --> 00:20:15.005
A weapon's form is its function.

366
00:20:15.589 --> 00:20:17.424
That's what makes them cool.

367
00:20:17.507 --> 00:20:21.178
You're right. Gaia.
And I'm still excited by this dojo.

368
00:20:22.804 --> 00:20:24.556
You're amazing. Sensei.

369
00:20:24.640 --> 00:20:27.809
A dojo you come to every day
still excites you.

370
00:20:27.893 --> 00:20:30.187
That's what makes you. Motobe.

371
00:20:30.854 --> 00:20:32.522
It's what makes you a genius.

372
00:20:33.857 --> 00:20:36.318
[Motobe] This is just my toy box.
this dojo.

373
00:20:36.985 --> 00:20:39.655
And also. it's a safe space.

374
00:20:39.738 --> 00:20:41.490
What do you mean. "a safe space"?

375
00:20:41.990 --> 00:20:46.578
We have rules.
and discipline. and common sense.

376
00:20:46.662 --> 00:20:50.082
I assure you
it's a much safer place than out there.

377
00:20:50.165 --> 00:20:52.167
But while we're here. Gaia.

378
00:20:52.668 --> 00:20:54.378
it's been far too long.

379
00:20:54.461 --> 00:20:56.088
How about a sparring session?

380
00:20:56.171 --> 00:20:58.090
[Gaia gasps softly]

381
00:20:59.424 --> 00:21:00.759
Sensei.

382
00:21:01.385 --> 00:21:04.596
turns out the dojo's not
a safe space after all.

383
00:21:05.722 --> 00:21:09.226
-["Mountain Top" by Novel core playing]
-[lyrics in Japanese]

384
00:22:18.128 --> 00:22:19.254
[in English] ♪ Yeah ♪

385
00:22:19.338 --> 00:22:21.965
♪ Yeah. yeah ♪

386
00:22:22.466 --> 00:22:24.634
♪ I'm on the mountaintop. yeah ♪

387
00:22:25.469 --> 00:22:27.971
♪ Yeah. yeah ♪

388
00:22:28.513 --> 00:22:30.682
♪ I'm on the mountaintop. yeah ♪

389
00:22:33.060 --> 00:22:35.103
[music fades]
